{"word":"αὐδή","slug":"αὐδή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αὐδή</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the human voice, speech</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>ὀμφή</el> (a divine voice), <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the sound</i> or <i>twang</i> of the bowstring, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; of a trumpet, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; of the <el>τέττιξ</el>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:φήμη'><el>φήμη</el></a>, <i>a report, account</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>an oracle</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}